      #generalstartup
        h4 General Startup Questions
        #accordion3.panel-group
          .panel.panel-default
            .panel-heading
              h4.panel-title(data-toggle="collapse", data-target="#3_1")
                | What is investing in businesses about?
            |         
            #3_1.panel-collapse.collapse
              .panel-body
                | Investing in businesses is about picking businesses that you believe have the potential to grow. You invest in exchange for a portion of their equity, meaning that you buy shares in the business. If a business you've invested in succeeds, the shares that you own will become worth more than you paid for them. However, if the business fails - as the majority of early-stage businesses do - you'll lose your investment.
          |     
          |     
          .panel.panel-default
            .panel-heading
              h4.panel-title(data-toggle="collapse", data-target="#3_2")
                | Do businesses issue shares directly to investors?
            |         
            #3_2.panel-collapse.collapse
              .panel-body
                | Yes.
          |     
          .panel.panel-default
            .panel-heading
              h4.panel-title(data-toggle="collapse", data-target="#3_3")
                | If businesses issue shares directly to investors, what does FundMyVenture do?
            |         
            #3_3.panel-collapse.collapse
              .panel-body
                | We help connect you with people who are interested in investing in early stage businesses. We understand that building a startup is hard, so we want that as an entrepreneur you spend all your energy working on your product and let us bring you interested people who are willing to help you out in the journey, be it through financial funding or contributing via sweat equity or both!
